{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6075de3e-c387-4585-b05b-dfe0051d292f","content":"**Yes, you will hit a compatibility issue.** MSTest v4 (4.x) dropped support for .NET 6.0 — it requires **net8.0** or later.\n\nYour project currently targets `net6.0` with MSTest 3.8.0. To upgrade to MSTest v4 you'd need to also retarget to at least `net8.0`.\n\nNote that .NET 6 reached end-of-life in November 2024, so upgrading the TFM is generally recommended regardless.\n\n**Your options:**\n\n1. **Upgrade both** — change `TargetFramework` to `net8.0` (or `net9.0`) and bump MSTest to `4.x`.\n2. **Stay on net6.0** — remain on MSTest 3.x.\n\nWant me to perform the upgrade?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"089b34bb-094d-4f8f-9d0e-50d100762b92","outputTokens":200},"id":"870e6570-bf53-457a-a6bd-f7020e9fbb5a","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:21:52.757Z","parentId":"f4c5f7a6-9504-4c07-bf14-cd6be56e817e"}
